The paper deals with a stochastic threshold group testing problem, which involves testing subsets of items and identifying a subset of defective items. This problem is motivated by biological applications, but the paper focuses on the computational aspects of designing and implementing testing schemes. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
